cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NA, cs.AI, cs.DS 

The paper deals with learning a regression model parameterized by a fixed-rank positive semidefinite matrix, which is a problem commonly encountered in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of gradient descent algorithms and Riemannian geometry, which are relevant to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper applies the proposed algorithms to the problem of learning a distance function, which is a topic in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
